1
00:00:04,271 --> 00:00:07,208
⟨A housewife who was cheated on by her husband and a bar mom who is a literary geek →

2
00:00:07,274 --> 00:00:09,210
Fulfilling a fateful encounter⟩

3
00:00:09,276 --> 00:00:11,212
(Kiwako) Kazuto has passed away.

4
00:00:11,278 --> 00:00:13,714
(Luna) This was the last work I read.

5
00:00:13,781 --> 00:00:16,717
⟨My ex-boyfriend Kazuto through his trip to Osaka→

6
00:00:16,784 --> 00:00:19,720
Ryoko learns of the gentle lie⟩

7
00:00:19,787 --> 00:00:24,225
⟨But Luna has a secret that she has been hiding from Ryoko...⟩

8
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:27,795
⟨“Moonlit Journey” Already reaches the climax⟩

9
00:00:34,268 --> 00:00:36,203
(Kikuo) Ryoko.

10
00:00:36,270 --> 00:00:40,207
(Ryoko) What, Kikuo-san!?

11
00:00:40,274 --> 00:00:42,710
Why….

12
00:00:42,777 --> 00:00:45,212
(Kikuo) I came to pick you up.

13
00:00:45,279 --> 00:00:48,215
Hear it from her.

14
00:00:48,282 --> 00:00:51,218
(Ryoko) Huh?

15
00:00:51,285 --> 00:00:56,223
>> Mr. Sosuke Shigehara is the author I am in charge of.

16
00:00:56,290 --> 00:00:58,793
(Ryoko) Shigehara...

17
00:01:00,795 --> 00:01:04,165
(Luna) I'm sorry for being silent until now.

18
00:01:04,231 --> 00:01:07,168
The fact that I am Sosuke Shigehara is →

19
00:01:07,234 --> 00:01:11,172
Only a few people in the publishing industry know about it.

20
00:01:11,238 --> 00:01:16,177
``Shigehara'' is the name of the place in Aichi Prefecture where my mother's parents live.

21
00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:20,681
“Sosuke” has different characters, but →

22
00:01:20,748 --> 00:01:23,684
This is the name before changing the family register.

23
00:01:23,751 --> 00:01:26,687
15 years since receiving the award →

24
00:01:26,754 --> 00:01:32,193
I have continued to work as a writer under this pen name.

25
00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:37,698
Lately I've been in a slump and can't think of a topic for my next work →

26
00:01:37,765 --> 00:01:42,703
I consulted with Mr. Sawatsuji, who has been in charge of the matter for many years.

27
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:46,207
Mr. Sawatsuji also responded to my sudden call →

28
00:01:46,273 --> 00:01:48,709
He gave me an idea →

29
00:01:48,776 --> 00:01:51,212
It has to come from within →

30
00:01:51,278 --> 00:01:56,283
I was hitting a wall thinking that there was no point in it.

31
00:01:58,285 --> 00:02:03,224
I'm really sorry for making you suspect that I was cheating on you.

32
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:08,662
Mr. Sawatsuji is a serious person who is devoted to his work.

33
00:02:08,729 --> 00:02:11,165
The night Ryoko came to the store →

34
00:02:11,232 --> 00:02:14,168
I was the one who called Mr. Sawatsuji.

35
00:02:14,235 --> 00:02:17,671
📱〔I'm at the store today, so please come by now〕

36
00:02:17,738 --> 00:02:20,674
>> [Called by Professor Shigehara] (Ryoko) [What? Starting now? ]

37
00:02:20,741 --> 00:02:24,178
(Luna) After talking at the coffee shop, when I returned to the shop→

38
00:02:24,245 --> 00:02:27,681
Ryoko was just there.

39
00:02:27,748 --> 00:02:31,185
[Nice to meet you, my name is Luna]

40
00:02:31,252 --> 00:02:35,189
(Ryoko) Then, who is the Akina on that business card?

41
00:02:35,256 --> 00:02:39,193
(Luna) Akina from Shuffle about 6 months ago →

42
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:42,196
Mr. Sawatsuji wants to use that restaurant for entertaining →

43
00:02:42,263 --> 00:02:44,198
I just introduced it.

44
00:02:44,265 --> 00:02:49,203
>> After the entertainment, I just called him once to thank him.

45
00:02:49,270 --> 00:02:51,705
(Luna) When Ryoko came to Marquee Moon →

46
00:02:51,772 --> 00:02:55,209
I knew it was Mr. Sawatsuji's wife.

47
00:02:55,276 --> 00:02:58,712
But I'm keeping my identity a secret →

48
00:02:58,779 --> 00:03:01,715
I couldn't tell you about my relationship with Mr. Sawatsuji.

49
00:03:01,782 --> 00:03:03,717
>>That night→

50
00:03:03,784 --> 00:03:06,654
I got a call from my teacher. 📱 [Vibration sound]

51
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,656
〔hello? ]

52
00:03:08,722 --> 00:03:12,159
📱 [My wife Ryoko (Luna) is coming to the store now]

53
00:03:12,226 --> 00:03:13,661
>> [Eh? ]

54
00:03:13,727 --> 00:03:17,164
(Luna) [I decided to go on a journey with her]

55
00:03:17,231 --> 00:03:18,666
>> [Huh? ]

56
00:03:18,732 --> 00:03:20,668
(Luna) [Research trip]

57
00:03:20,734 --> 00:03:23,170
[I think I'll find something to write about]

58
00:03:23,237 --> 00:03:25,673
>> [No, even if you suddenly say that]

59
00:03:25,739 --> 00:03:27,675
[What, what does my wife say? ]

60
00:03:27,741 --> 00:03:30,177
(Luna) [I haven't talked about the details yet]

61
00:03:30,244 --> 00:03:33,681
[But even she needs a break]

62
00:03:33,747 --> 00:03:37,184
[Don't you think so? 〕 📱〔No, it's a day off...〕

63
00:03:37,251 --> 00:03:42,189
(Luna) [This trip should be meaningful for her as well]

64
00:03:42,256 --> 00:03:46,760
[I won't do anything wrong, so could you leave it to me? ]

65
00:03:48,762 --> 00:03:54,702
(Ryoko) Does that mean I was fooled by two people?

66
00:03:54,768 --> 00:03:57,204
(Luna) Mr. Sawatsuji is not bad.

67
00:03:57,271 --> 00:04:02,710
I was the one who asked Ryoko not to contact me during the trip.

68
00:04:02,776 --> 00:04:04,645
>> No, it's my fault too.

69
00:04:04,712 --> 00:04:07,648
The reason why I didn't follow Ryoko at all was →

70
00:04:07,715 --> 00:04:11,652
I think it was bad after all.

71
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:14,221
sorry.

72
00:04:17,224 --> 00:04:19,727
(Ryoko) Huh...｡

73
00:04:21,729 --> 00:04:23,664
Huh...

74
00:04:23,731 --> 00:04:25,666
That's enough.

75
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:32,172
As my mom said, it was a very meaningful trip.

76
00:04:32,239 --> 00:04:34,174
(Luna) Ryoko-san…｡

77
00:04:34,241 --> 00:04:38,679
(Ryoko) Mom: Do you think you can write a novel?

78
00:04:38,746 --> 00:04:42,683
(Luna) Yes, I was actually writing while traveling.

79
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:46,687
I sent the first draft to Mr. Sawatsuji this morning.

80
00:04:46,754 --> 00:04:48,756
(Ryoko) Good.

81
00:04:50,257 --> 00:04:52,192
Mr. Kikuo.

82
00:04:52,259 --> 00:04:56,697
Thank you for coming to pick me up.

83
00:04:56,764 --> 00:05:01,201
>> Well... at least that much.

84
00:05:01,268 --> 00:05:03,771
Ah...｡

85
00:05:05,205 --> 00:05:09,143
(Luna) Well then, you two, please go home first.

86
00:05:09,209 --> 00:05:12,146
I have somewhere to go for a while.

87
00:05:12,212 --> 00:05:15,149
(Ryoko) Huh? Another literary spot?

88
00:05:15,215 --> 00:05:16,650
(Luna) That's correct.

89
00:05:16,717 --> 00:05:20,654
I've always wanted to go to the Yasunari Kawabata Literary Museum.

90
00:05:20,721 --> 00:05:25,159
>> The teacher also likes Yasunari Kawabata, the Literary Museum. It's really good.

91
00:05:25,225 --> 00:05:27,728
(Luna) Yes, I'm looking forward to it.

92
00:05:32,232 --> 00:05:35,169
>> Well then. (Ryoko) Mom, see you soon.

93
00:05:35,235 --> 00:05:37,237
(Luna) Goodbye.

94
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:44,678
>>Would you like to have something to eat when you arrive in Tokyo? Sometimes it's just the two of us.

95
00:05:44,745 --> 00:05:47,181
(Ryoko) Yeah, let's go.

96
00:05:47,247 --> 00:05:50,184
⟨I noticed it later⟩

97
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:53,687
⟨At that time, mom didn't say "See you later" →

98
00:05:53,754 --> 00:05:56,757
I said “goodbye”⟩

99
00:06:04,565 --> 00:06:06,500
(Ryoko) Ah, it was delicious.

100
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:10,003
It's been about 20 years since I came here?

101
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:14,007
>> No, I'm sure he hasn't come since we got married →

102
00:06:14,074 --> 00:06:18,579
It's been 21 years. (Ryoko) Ha, is it already like that?

103
00:06:20,581 --> 00:06:25,018
>> I know this is late, but happy birthday.

104
00:06:25,085 --> 00:06:28,522
(Ryoko) Huh? Did you remember?

105
00:06:28,589 --> 00:06:33,026
>> This is an excuse, but around the time Atsushi was born →

106
00:06:33,093 --> 00:06:35,529
When I asked, “What are you going to do for your birthday?”→

107
00:06:35,596 --> 00:06:38,532
I was told, ``That's enough.''

108
00:06:38,599 --> 00:06:44,104
(Ryoko) Did I say that? Ha... I don't remember.

109
00:06:45,606 --> 00:06:49,042
>> I was severely scolded by Mr. Shigehara.

110
00:06:49,109 --> 00:06:52,045
I wonder if there's anyone who would take that seriously.

111
00:06:52,112 --> 00:06:53,981
sorry.

112
00:06:54,047 --> 00:06:57,484
(Ryoko) Oh no.

113
00:06:57,551 --> 00:07:00,554
Can I open it? >>Of course.

114
00:07:03,056 --> 00:07:06,994
(Ryoko) Eh, this is really expensive, right?

115
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:09,496
>> Because it's 17 years worth.

116
00:07:09,563 --> 00:07:14,501
No, I was thinking about it, but I thought it would be more of a watch than an accessory.

117
00:07:14,568 --> 00:07:20,574
What can I say... I want to continue spending time with you.

118
00:07:23,577 --> 00:07:26,013
(Ryoko) Thank you.

119
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:29,016
happy.

120
00:07:29,082 --> 00:07:31,084
I'll take care of it.

121
00:07:37,090 --> 00:07:39,593
>> Haha... (Ryoko) Haha.

122
00:07:41,595 --> 00:07:44,531
I have to thank my mom.

123
00:07:44,598 --> 00:07:47,534
Mama...

124
00:07:47,601 --> 00:07:53,473
What kind of novel did Mr. Shigehara write on this trip?

125
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:57,478
>> Ah~ Female buddy is traveling in Osaka →

126
00:07:57,544 --> 00:08:01,481
Encountering an incident in a place related to literature→

127
00:08:01,548 --> 00:08:03,550
I guess it's something to solve.

128
00:08:06,053 --> 00:08:12,492
(Ryoko) Have you asked why the setting is Osaka?

129
00:08:12,559 --> 00:08:18,565
>> Well... after reading the novel, it's kind of like that.

130
00:08:21,568 --> 00:08:25,505
(Ryoko) Will you listen to me?

131
00:08:25,572 --> 00:08:27,507
>>Yes.

132
00:08:27,574 --> 00:08:33,580
(Ryoko) ⟨I told you all the truths I learned about Kazuto in Osaka⟩

133
00:08:35,582 --> 00:08:38,518
⟨My husband accepted everything⟩

134
00:08:38,585 --> 00:08:51,532
♪～

135
00:08:51,598 --> 00:08:55,969
(Ryoko) I'm sorry for being away for so long and worrying you.

136
00:08:56,036 --> 00:08:57,971
(Haruko) I heard that.

137
00:08:58,038 --> 00:09:01,475
(Haruko) Did you accompany the writer on his reporting trip?

138
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:04,478
(Yoshika) If that's the case, you should just say that from the beginning.

139
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:08,482
(Atsushi) That's serious. (Ryoko) I'm really sorry.

140
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:12,486
(Kikuo) No, your father should have explained it to you sooner.

141
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:15,989
sorry.

142
00:09:16,056 --> 00:09:17,991
Good~

143
00:09:18,058 --> 00:09:20,994
Now I can go back to Saitama with peace of mind.

144
00:09:21,061 --> 00:09:23,497
(Ryoko) Thank you very much, mom.

145
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:26,500
>> I bought a tart, so let's all eat it together.

146
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:31,004
That's crazy. It's Quile Favor Bon. (Atsushi) Eh, what kind of flavor?

147
00:09:31,071 --> 00:09:34,074
(Haruko) I'll make some tea. (Aromatic) Milk is good.

148
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:39,079
(sound of opening a drawer)

149
00:09:44,084 --> 00:09:49,523
(Ryoko) ⟨Thanks to Kazuto's kind lie, I was able to find my current happiness⟩

150
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:54,094
⟨From now on, let's live each day to the fullest⟩

151
00:09:59,099 --> 00:10:02,035
(Ryoko's voice) ``I just got home safely.

152
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:04,104
Thank you for everything.”

153
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:11,545
(Ryoko) ⟨Even after a few days, I didn't receive a reply from mom⟩

154
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:16,049
Huh... I guess you're busy. (Sound of descending stairs)

155
00:10:16,116 --> 00:10:19,553
(Atsushi) Dad, are you late today too? (Ryoko) Huh? what up?

156
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:23,056
>> Just wanted to talk about homework.

157
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:26,059
(Ryoko) Wow, what kind of homework is that unusual?

158
00:10:26,126 --> 00:10:28,562
>> Book review.

159
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:31,565
I don't know what to read.

160
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:33,066
(Ryoko) Ha.

161
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:37,137
Well then, why don't you ask someone who knows a lot about literature?

162
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:46,580
(Bubbly) Ryoko-san. (Ryoko) Bubbly-chan It's been a while!

163
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:48,081
what happened?

164
00:10:48,148 --> 00:10:51,084
(Bubbly) Mom is gone.

165
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:52,586
(Ryoko) Huh?

166
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:56,023
(Bubly's voice) When I came back, nothing much had changed.

167
00:10:56,089 --> 00:10:58,025
He seemed fine.

168
00:10:58,091 --> 00:11:02,029
(Luna) [I'm sorry for leaving the shop to you right now]

169
00:11:02,095 --> 00:11:06,533
>> [How was Osaka? ] (Luna) [Yes, I'm glad I went]

170
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:09,536
[Thank you] ☏ [Ringtone]

171
00:11:09,603 --> 00:11:12,039
[Yes, it's Marquee Moon]

172
00:11:12,105 --> 00:11:15,542
☏(Male) [Is mom coming today? ]

173
00:11:15,609 --> 00:11:20,547
[Um... which one are you? ]

174
00:11:20,614 --> 00:11:24,051
☏ [Sound of disconnected call]

175
00:11:24,117 --> 00:11:28,555
(Bubly's voice) After that, I received many silent calls.

176
00:11:28,622 --> 00:11:32,059
(Customer) [I'll be back again, good night] (Luna) [Thank you]

177
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:45,072
♪～

178
00:11:45,138 --> 00:11:47,074
(Luna) [Ah, Bubbly-chan→

179
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:50,077
Will you be able to attend the meeting with the reformer tomorrow? ]

180
00:11:50,143 --> 00:11:54,081
>> [Of course] (Luna) [Please come from 5pm]

181
00:11:55,582 --> 00:11:59,586
(Bubly's voice) But the next day, mom didn't come.

182
00:12:01,588 --> 00:12:03,523
(Ryoko) I wonder what happened...

183
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:07,027
>> Maybe he got caught up in something weird.

184
00:12:07,094 --> 00:12:09,029
(Ryoko) No way…｡

185
00:12:09,096 --> 00:12:13,033
(Kikuo) Ah~ Come to think of it, I haven't received any replies at all.

186
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:16,036
I'm asking for a meeting date.

187
00:12:16,103 --> 00:12:18,538
(Ryoko) So, Kikuo-san hasn't been able to contact you either?

188
00:12:18,605 --> 00:12:23,043
>> Hmm, well, I'm pretty much like that on a regular basis.

189
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:26,113
It may be unusual for us to have so little contact.

190
00:12:28,115 --> 00:12:30,117
(Luna) [Goodbye]

191
00:12:35,622 --> 00:12:38,058
(Ryoko) Huh…｡ (Monitor) Now we have a guest…｡

192
00:12:38,125 --> 00:12:41,061
Ah, Satsuki Nanami is appearing. (Monitor) Former Japanese badminton representative→

193
00:12:41,128 --> 00:12:43,563
Satsuki Nanami came to visit us.

194
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:46,566
(Yoshika) Mom: I didn't know you played Bud.

195
00:12:46,633 --> 00:12:50,070
Moreover, the Olympic athletes are really serious.

196
00:12:50,137 --> 00:12:51,571
(Ryoko) An old story.

197
00:12:51,638 --> 00:12:55,008
>> But isn't it great that he's friends with Satsuki Nanami?

198
00:12:55,075 --> 00:13:01,515
(Ryoko) I guess we're friends already, but we haven't been in touch.

199
00:13:01,581 --> 00:13:03,517
Yes, I was able to do it.

200
00:13:03,583 --> 00:13:06,019
(Aroma) Eh, even a pair aiming for the Olympics →

201
00:13:06,086 --> 00:13:08,522
That's how it turns out.

202
00:13:08,588 --> 00:13:12,025
I want to be friends with my current best friend forever.

203
00:13:12,092 --> 00:13:13,527
(Ryoko) That's right.

204
00:13:13,593 --> 00:13:16,029
(Monitor) (Caster) Yuria Katayose, a popular influenza influencer →

205
00:13:16,096 --> 00:13:20,033
This is a follow-up report on an incident in which a man was attacked and injured by a fan.

206
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:22,035
(Aromatic) This is really scary.

207
00:13:22,102 --> 00:13:25,038
Even though it's dangerous, if people notice it, I'll get stuck.

208
00:13:25,105 --> 00:13:29,042
(Monitor) I have been bothered by repeated silent calls...

209
00:13:29,109 --> 00:13:32,045
[I received many silent calls]

210
00:13:32,112 --> 00:13:36,550
(Monitor) Well, tomorrow, March 3rd, there will be a total lunar eclipse.

211
00:13:36,616 --> 00:13:38,552
(Aromatic) What is a total lunar eclipse?

212
00:13:38,618 --> 00:13:40,554
📱(Vibration sound) (Fragrance) So what is totality?

213
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:43,056
(Atsushi) That's why I asked you to listen to the explanation.

214
00:13:43,123 --> 00:13:48,562
(Bubly's voice) "Did you hear from mom? I'm anxious and worried..."

215
00:13:48,628 --> 00:13:51,064
(Sound of door opening) Ryoko!

216
00:13:51,131 --> 00:13:54,501
(Ryoko) Bubbly-chan, are you okay? >> Should I report it to the police?

217
00:13:54,568 --> 00:13:56,503
(Ryoko) Hmm...｡

218
00:13:56,570 --> 00:14:00,006
Why don't you ask your mom's friends first?

219
00:14:00,073 --> 00:14:02,576
>> Friends...｡

220
00:14:03,577 --> 00:14:07,080
(Bubbly) \I don't know much about my mom's private life/

221
00:14:08,582 --> 00:14:11,017
(Tamura) Excuse me~ Ah.

222
00:14:11,084 --> 00:14:14,521
(Ryoko) Ah! friend!

223
00:14:14,588 --> 00:14:16,523
(Tamura) Huh?

224
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:21,528
(Ryoko) Transferred to Tokyo... That happens even to detectives.

225
00:14:21,595 --> 00:14:24,030
(Tamura) To be precise, it's training.

226
00:14:24,097 --> 00:14:27,534
I will be working with the Metropolitan Police Department for two years from April.

227
00:14:27,601 --> 00:14:30,537
>>What do you think about mom?

228
00:14:30,604 --> 00:14:34,541
(Tamura) I can't make a judgment on the nature of the incident yet.

229
00:14:34,608 --> 00:14:37,544
(Ryoko) Tamura-san hasn't been able to contact me either, right?

230
00:14:37,611 --> 00:14:42,048
(Tamura) I can't say anything because I only got an answering machine once.

231
00:14:42,115 --> 00:14:47,053
>> Mom has big eyes and isn't she beautiful?

232
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,555
(Ryoko) Yes.

233
00:14:48,622 --> 00:14:51,558
>> In a novel I read a long time ago, there was a man who was stalking →

234
00:14:51,625 --> 00:14:56,496
There's something about a woman's dark eyes that makes me want to swim naked in the lake.

235
00:14:56,563 --> 00:15:00,000
Ah, that's disgusting! What should I do! What if my mom was noticed even though she was weird?

236
00:15:00,066 --> 00:15:03,503
(Ryoko) Bubbly-chan, calm down.

237
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:06,506
(Meguru) Good morning! (Bubbly) Ah, Meguru-chan.

238
00:15:06,573 --> 00:15:11,578
There was a strange man wandering around there right now.

239
00:15:16,082 --> 00:15:18,518
(Bubbly) Ah! Now!

240
00:15:18,585 --> 00:15:21,087
The man who was wandering around!

241
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:26,593
there was! Wait!

242
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,602
(Tamura) Hey!

243
00:15:42,609 --> 00:15:44,611
(Tamura) Wait!

244
00:15:47,614 --> 00:15:49,549
>> Ah...!

245
00:15:49,616 --> 00:15:51,551
(Tamura) Why did you run away?

246
00:15:51,618 --> 00:15:53,553
>> No... that...

247
00:15:55,055 --> 00:15:57,991
(Tamura) What's the purpose of going to that store?

248
00:15:58,058 --> 00:16:03,063
(Male) What... How can I become a customer of that store?

249
00:16:04,564 --> 00:16:07,500
(Ryoko) I mean, I've been wondering about this for a while now →

250
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:11,004
You mean you didn't have the courage to go in and just wandered around?

251
00:16:11,071 --> 00:16:15,008
(Sakurai) There are some beautiful mothers out there, and I've always been interested in them.

252
00:16:15,075 --> 00:16:20,513
But I guess places like this don't accept the first customers.

253
00:16:20,580 --> 00:16:23,016
We welcome everyone.

254
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:25,018
Mom always says that.

255
00:16:25,085 --> 00:16:27,520
It's no good to get excited just by regulars.

256
00:16:27,587 --> 00:16:31,524
Let's make this a store that even first-time customers can enjoy.

257
00:16:31,591 --> 00:16:34,094
(Tamura) Hmm, sounds like Noppy.

258
00:16:35,595 --> 00:16:38,531
(Sakurai) I'm sorry for making silent calls so many times.

259
00:16:38,598 --> 00:16:41,534
From now on, I will come to the store confidently.

260
00:16:41,601 --> 00:16:44,037
I'll be waiting for you. >> Yes!

261
00:16:44,104 --> 00:16:47,107
Please excuse me. >> See you soon.

262
00:16:48,608 --> 00:16:53,046
(Sound of door closing) (Ryoko) Does that mean the stalker theory is gone?

263
00:16:53,113 --> 00:16:57,484
>> But why did you skip the reform meeting...

264
00:16:57,550 --> 00:16:59,986
(Meguru) Oh, that's crazy!

265
00:17:00,053 --> 00:17:01,988
What's wrong?

266
00:17:02,055 --> 00:17:05,492
I forgot to pass on the message from mom.

267
00:17:05,558 --> 00:17:08,495
I'll leave the meeting to Mr. Bubbly.

268
00:17:08,561 --> 00:17:11,498
Huh!? Why didn't you say something so important?

269
00:17:11,564 --> 00:17:13,500
Sorry! >> Hey!

270
00:17:13,566 --> 00:17:17,504
(Ryoko) Bubbly-chan, you really love your mom.

271
00:17:17,570 --> 00:17:21,007
>> That's right, he's a benefactor.

272
00:17:21,074 --> 00:17:24,010
(Tamura) Benefactor? >> Yes.

273
00:17:24,077 --> 00:17:29,015
I was tricked into debt by a bad person.

274
00:17:29,082 --> 00:17:33,086
But mom came to help me.

275
00:17:35,588 --> 00:17:39,592
(Man) [You can't run away! ] [Give it back quickly, Ola! ]

276
00:17:41,094 --> 00:17:43,530
(Luna) [Align your ears and return it]

277
00:17:43,596 --> 00:17:46,032
[There's nothing to complain about, right? ]

278
00:17:46,099 --> 00:17:48,101
(Male) [Let's go]

279
00:17:55,542 --> 00:17:57,977
[Are you stupid? ]

280
00:17:58,044 --> 00:18:00,980
[I didn't ask you to help me]

281
00:18:01,047 --> 00:18:04,484
(Luna) [I'm sure you weren't asked to do it]

282
00:18:04,551 --> 00:18:07,987
>> [I'm glad he died]

283
00:18:08,054 --> 00:18:11,491
[There's no point in living for a scumbag like me.]

284
00:18:11,558 --> 00:18:17,997
(Luna) [Hmmm, first of all, I'm not trash, and I think there's a meaning to being alive.]

285
00:18:18,064 --> 00:18:19,999
>> [Eh? ]

286
00:18:20,066 --> 00:18:23,503
(Luna) [Because you're funny]

287
00:18:23,570 --> 00:18:26,005
>> [Interesting? ]

288
00:18:26,072 --> 00:18:30,009
(Luna) [Ah, but I just lent you the money, so be sure to pay it back]

289
00:18:30,076 --> 00:18:32,011
[It doesn't matter how many years it takes]

290
00:18:32,078 --> 00:18:34,013
>> [Maybe I'll betray you? ]

291
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:36,015
(Luna) [That time is that time]

292
00:18:36,082 --> 00:18:39,586
[But you don't do that]

293
00:18:45,592 --> 00:18:48,027
>> Getting people to believe in you →

294
00:18:48,094 --> 00:18:51,531
I thought it was such a joy.

295
00:18:51,598 --> 00:18:55,468
(Tamura) Noppy: You can see that he's very affectionate.

296
00:18:55,535 --> 00:18:56,970
(Ryoko) Yes.

297
00:18:57,036 --> 00:19:02,475
(Tamura) However, I hardly talk about myself.

298
00:19:02,542 --> 00:19:06,980
When we were all watching TV on a school trip →

299
00:19:07,046 --> 00:19:09,482
A popular transgender talent has emerged.

300
00:19:09,549 --> 00:19:11,985
(Monitor) [Don't say that! >>Wait a minute...]

301
00:19:12,051 --> 00:19:14,487
[I'm glad I don't have people like this around.]

302
00:19:14,554 --> 00:19:17,991
[Not really, but it looks like fun, so that's good.]

303
00:19:18,057 --> 00:19:21,494
[No, I can't do it] (Classmate) [Takashi-kun...]

304
00:19:21,561 --> 00:19:27,500
(Tamura's voice) The person who said it was impossible was someone who was close to Noppy.

305
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:31,571
That night, Noppi was nowhere to be seen.

306
00:19:33,072 --> 00:19:36,576
[Hey, what are you doing! ]

307
00:19:40,079 --> 00:19:42,515
(Tamura's voice) That guy turned around and said.

308
00:19:42,582 --> 00:19:46,519
"I was just looking at the moon."

309
00:19:46,586 --> 00:19:51,591
When I saw her forced smile, I couldn't say anything.

310
00:19:56,596 --> 00:19:59,532
(Tamura's voice) When I found out my name was Luna→

311
00:19:59,599 --> 00:20:03,036
I remembered that night.

312
00:20:03,102 --> 00:20:06,039
Because I'm the one who carries it all by myself →

313
00:20:06,105 --> 00:20:10,043
I thought it was great to have someone like Ryoko.

314
00:20:10,109 --> 00:20:12,545
but….

315
00:20:12,612 --> 00:20:14,547
(Ryoko) But?

316
00:20:14,614 --> 00:20:20,053
(Tamura) Actually, when he left Osaka, the two of us had dinner together.

317
00:20:20,119 --> 00:20:22,555
(Luna) [Ah, have you decided on a room yet? ]

318
00:20:22,622 --> 00:20:25,558
(Tamura) [Yeah, I'll go to the contract next week]

319
00:20:25,625 --> 00:20:28,561
[Ah, let's have dinner in Tokyo again, Ryoko-san...]

320
00:20:28,628 --> 00:20:30,563
>> [Sound of placing teacup]

321
00:20:30,630 --> 00:20:35,068
(Luna) [Hmm~ I don't think I'll see Ryoko again]

322
00:20:35,134 --> 00:20:38,071
(Ryoko) Huh... (Tamura) That's why →

323
00:20:38,137 --> 00:20:40,573
I thought they were in a fight or something.

324
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:44,577
(Ryoko) I didn't. That's not the case at all.

325
00:20:44,644 --> 00:20:47,146
Huh...

326
00:20:49,148 --> 00:20:54,520
I see, you're just an interview subject...

327
00:20:54,587 --> 00:20:56,022
(Luna) [It's "Manji"]

328
00:20:56,089 --> 00:20:58,024
[Can't read because it's out of focus! ]

329
00:20:58,091 --> 00:21:00,526
[It suits you very well] (Ryoko) [Aha]

330
00:21:00,593 --> 00:21:04,097
(Luna) [Happy birthday! ]

331
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:12,105
(Luna) [Ryoko-san, leave it as is... it's fine as is]

332
00:21:14,107 --> 00:21:16,042
(Tamura) Huh?

333
00:21:16,109 --> 00:21:19,545
(Ryoko) Oh no.

334
00:21:19,612 --> 00:21:26,119
That's the kind of person I was to my mom.

335
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:29,055
Huh...

336
00:21:29,122 --> 00:21:32,625
(Bubbly) Ryoko-san, that's not true.

337
00:21:35,128 --> 00:21:37,063
Mom told me.

338
00:21:37,130 --> 00:21:41,634
(Bubly's voice) Ryoko is my dream.

339
00:21:46,639 --> 00:21:52,078
I accidentally caused a small scratch on this.

340
00:21:52,145 --> 00:21:55,014
They said you can't use it at the store so you can take it home.

341
00:21:55,081 --> 00:21:59,085
My mom told me to give it to Ryoko.

342
00:22:05,591 --> 00:22:09,095
(Ryoko) Am I my mom's dream?

343
00:22:10,596 --> 00:22:12,532
(Kikuo) I'm home.

344
00:22:12,598 --> 00:22:15,535
(Ryoko) Welcome back. >> What? That glass.

345
00:22:15,601 --> 00:22:18,538
(Ryoko) Mom bought it in Osaka.

346
00:22:18,604 --> 00:22:21,541
Glass, paintings, sculptures, etc.→

347
00:22:21,607 --> 00:22:25,044
Contracts for renovations and reservation apps are also available.

348
00:22:25,111 --> 00:22:29,048
I was buying all the things I needed at the store.

349
00:22:29,115 --> 00:22:31,050
>> That's amazing.

350
00:22:31,117 --> 00:22:34,053
It's more of a shopping trip than a reporting trip.

351
00:22:34,120 --> 00:22:39,559
We covered the transportation and hotel expenses at our own expense.

352
00:22:39,625 --> 00:22:41,627
(Ryoko) Huh?

353
00:22:43,129 --> 00:22:46,566
>> This glass is so stylish.

354
00:22:46,632 --> 00:22:48,568
(Ryoko) Darling...

355
00:22:48,634 --> 00:22:51,070
(Luna) [Then I'll have Darling take the hotel.]

356
00:22:51,137 --> 00:22:54,507
[Oh, don't worry, I'll ask Darling to cover your travel expenses]

357
00:22:54,574 --> 00:22:58,010
(Ryoko) [Does Darin have to pay for this as well? ] (Luna) [What do you think? ]

358
00:22:58,077 --> 00:23:03,082
(Ryoko) Is Kikuo-san your mom's darling?

359
00:23:04,584 --> 00:23:07,019
(Luna) [No fountain pen]

360
00:23:07,086 --> 00:23:10,022
[Ah, it's an important thing that I received from my darling]

361
00:23:10,089 --> 00:23:12,525
(Ryoko) [My mom, Darling, gave me a fountain pen→

362
00:23:12,592 --> 00:23:14,527
Does that mean you're supporting me? ]

363
00:23:14,594 --> 00:23:16,529
(Luna) [Darling is the most understanding person]

364
00:23:16,596 --> 00:23:18,531
(Ryoko) [Is it already long? ]

365
00:23:18,598 --> 00:23:22,034
(Luna) [Yes, quite a bit]

366
00:23:22,101 --> 00:23:25,104
(Ryoko) [Something nice~]

367
00:23:34,614 --> 00:23:36,616
📱(vibration sound)

368
00:23:38,618 --> 00:23:41,554
Ah, it's from Mr. Shigehara. (Ryoko) Huh?

369
00:23:41,621 --> 00:23:43,623
>> Have you finally arrived?

370
00:23:45,625 --> 00:23:50,062
``I would like to change the depiction of the moon in the final chapter.

371
00:23:50,129 --> 00:23:53,065
Please wait a little longer for the meeting."

372
00:23:53,132 --> 00:23:56,502
yeah? Isn't it a full moon?

373
00:23:56,569 --> 00:23:58,504
(Ryoko) What is that?

374
00:23:58,571 --> 00:24:02,008
>> This work is at the end of each chapter →

375
00:24:02,074 --> 00:24:06,512
There's a scene where the main character looks at the waxing and waning of the moon and thinks about it.

376
00:24:06,579 --> 00:24:11,017
I was told that the final chapter ends with a full moon.

377
00:24:11,083 --> 00:24:14,086
Ah, this is still a secret.

378
00:24:22,094 --> 00:24:24,096
(starting sound)

379
00:24:27,099 --> 00:24:28,601
(clicking sound)

380
00:24:29,602 --> 00:24:32,038
(Ryoko) Ah, this is it.

381
00:24:32,104 --> 00:24:34,540
(clicking sound)

382
00:24:34,607 --> 00:24:37,543
(Ryoko) ⟨Sosuke Shigehara's new work⟩

383
00:24:37,610 --> 00:24:43,049
⟨The main character goes on a trip to Osaka to settle his long-standing love →

384
00:24:43,115 --> 00:24:48,554
A story about solving incidents encountered in places associated with literature⟩

385
00:24:48,621 --> 00:24:53,059
⟨At first I thought it was about me and Kazuto⟩

386
00:24:53,125 --> 00:24:55,494
⟨But it's different⟩

387
00:24:55,561 --> 00:25:00,066
⟨This was Mom's own story⟩

388
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:19,352
>> [Yes]

389
00:25:20,853 --> 00:25:22,788
[Wannian pen]

390
00:25:22,855 --> 00:25:26,292
[Even if you write on a computer, if you are a writer, you should use a proper pen →

391
00:25:26,359 --> 00:25:28,794
I think it would be a good idea to keep one.]

392
00:25:28,861 --> 00:25:38,804
♪～

393
00:25:38,871 --> 00:25:42,308
(Kikuo's voice) "It's okay, I'm sure it'll work out."

394
00:25:42,375 --> 00:25:44,877
"Did you tell your parents?"

395
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:51,884
(Kikuo's voice) "I see. I hope someday we can face each other face to face."

396
00:25:57,323 --> 00:25:59,759
[Sound of door opening]

397
00:25:59,825 --> 00:26:03,763
[Congratulations on opening your store!]

398
00:26:03,829 --> 00:26:07,266
[Working hard as a writer and mom]

399
00:26:07,333 --> 00:26:09,268
(Luna) [Thank you]

400
00:26:09,335 --> 00:26:12,271
>> [It's a nice store]

401
00:26:12,338 --> 00:26:14,273
[That's what "marquee" is, right? ]

402
00:26:14,340 --> 00:26:17,777
[It's on the front of old American movie theaters and theaters →

403
00:26:17,843 --> 00:26:20,279
A big glowing signboard] (Luna) [Yes]

404
00:26:20,346 --> 00:26:23,783
[I want everyone to remember that they are the protagonists]

405
00:26:23,849 --> 00:26:25,284
>> [Main character? ]

406
00:26:25,351 --> 00:26:29,789
(Luna) [To live is to weave your own story]

407
00:26:29,855 --> 00:26:33,793
[Life is a story, everyone is the main character]

408
00:26:33,859 --> 00:26:38,297
[But there are many things that I don't think so]

409
00:26:38,364 --> 00:26:43,803
[Not being valued or treated unreasonably]

410
00:26:43,869 --> 00:26:45,805
[I was like that too]

411
00:26:45,871 --> 00:26:51,377
[My existence was denied and I had no place to belong]

412
00:26:53,379 --> 00:26:55,748
[The title of the performance is on the marquee →

413
00:26:55,815 --> 00:26:59,251
The name of the lead actor is displayed, right? ]

414
00:26:59,318 --> 00:27:01,754
[I've seen it in old Western movies.]

415
00:27:01,821 --> 00:27:04,757
[In front of a nostalgic movie theater→

416
00:27:04,824 --> 00:27:08,260
Shining billboards illuminated the city at night.

417
00:27:08,327 --> 00:27:10,262
[So is the moon]

418
00:27:10,329 --> 00:27:12,264
[No matter how dark the journey is→

419
00:27:12,331 --> 00:27:17,269
The moon continues to emit light behind the clouds and shines on people again.]

420
00:27:17,336 --> 00:27:20,840
[Both are the spotlight of life]

421
00:27:23,843 --> 00:27:26,278
>> [Wow...]

422
00:27:26,345 --> 00:27:30,783
(Luna) [It's my name that glitters on the marquee]

423
00:27:30,850 --> 00:27:33,786
[For those who come to my store→

424
00:27:33,853 --> 00:27:37,289
Remember that you are the main character →

425
00:27:37,356 --> 00:27:39,792
I want you to shine]

426
00:27:39,859 --> 00:27:42,795
[That's what I thought]

427
00:27:42,862 --> 00:27:46,866
>> [Like, really good! ]

428
00:27:54,373 --> 00:27:56,809
(Kikuo) [Hmm...]

429
00:27:56,876 --> 00:28:00,312
(Luna) [What the world wants from Sosuke Shigehara→

430
00:28:00,379 --> 00:28:02,314
This is what it means, right? ]

431
00:28:02,381 --> 00:28:06,819
>> [No, that's true, but is it really okay to leave it like this? ]

432
00:28:06,886 --> 00:28:08,821
(Luna) [Huh? ]

433
00:28:08,888 --> 00:28:12,324
>> [I am what comes up from within you→

434
00:28:12,391 --> 00:28:14,894
I would like you to write it.]

435
00:28:16,395 --> 00:28:21,834
📱 [Vibration sound] [Oh, sorry]

436
00:28:21,901 --> 00:28:25,838
[Yeah, ah~ sorry, sorry]

437
00:28:25,905 --> 00:28:29,341
[Yeah, I'm in a meeting right now]

438
00:28:29,408 --> 00:28:32,912
[Dinner is fine.]

439
00:28:34,914 --> 00:28:38,350
(Ryoko's voice) ``It's not like I want to end up with him.''

440
00:28:38,417 --> 00:28:40,853
I want to finish it properly.

441
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:43,422
I've always thought that way."

442
00:28:45,424 --> 00:28:48,360
(Luna's voice) ``The princess has gone to bed.''

443
00:28:48,427 --> 00:28:52,431
(Kikuo's voice) ``Please take care of my wife, who I apologize for caring for.''

444
00:28:55,868 --> 00:29:01,307
(Ryoko's voice) ``Even if I go back to Tokyo, the same thing will happen again.''

445
00:29:01,373 --> 00:29:36,342
♪～

446
00:29:36,408 --> 00:29:38,344
📱(vibration sound)

447
00:29:38,410 --> 00:29:40,346
(Ryoko) Ha! 📱(vibration sound)

448
00:29:40,412 --> 00:29:41,914
📱(vibration sound)

449
00:29:43,916 --> 00:29:45,918
(Ryoko) Hello, Mom!?

450
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:50,656
(Ryoko) Hello, Mom!?

451
00:29:50,723 --> 00:29:53,159
📱 I received a voicemail from Mr. Tamura (Luna).

452
00:29:53,225 --> 00:29:56,662
📱 Ryoko scolded me not to worry.

453
00:29:56,729 --> 00:30:00,166
📱 I wonder from what standpoint is that person speaking?

454
00:30:00,232 --> 00:30:02,168
(Ryoko) Hey mom, where are you now?

455
00:30:02,234 --> 00:30:05,671
(Luna) Don't worry, you're safe.

456
00:30:05,738 --> 00:30:08,174
📱 Wait!

457
00:30:09,675 --> 00:30:15,114
(Ryoko) Will I never see my mom again?

458
00:30:15,181 --> 00:30:17,616
(Luna) Do you think we can meet?

459
00:30:17,683 --> 00:30:21,187
I was deceiving you.

460
00:30:22,688 --> 00:30:27,193
(Ryoko) I read Mom's new book without permission.

461
00:30:29,828 --> 00:30:36,702
(Luna) The reason I took Ryoko on the trip wasn't just for interviews.

462
00:30:36,769 --> 00:30:41,273
I wanted to know what kind of person Mr. Sawatsuji's wife was.

463
00:30:42,775 --> 00:30:45,711
📱 A housewife from a normal family →

464
00:30:45,778 --> 00:30:51,217
(Luna) She suspects her husband of cheating on flimsy grounds and is pining for her ex-lover.

465
00:30:51,283 --> 00:30:56,222
To be honest, at first I thought, "Who is this person?"

466
00:30:56,288 --> 00:31:00,726
📱 If you are a dishonest person→

467
00:31:00,793 --> 00:31:05,231
I thought Mr. Sawatsuji should leave you.

468
00:31:05,297 --> 00:31:07,733
📱 But...｡

469
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:11,237
Ryoko was a nice person.

470
00:31:11,303 --> 00:31:14,240
(Luna's voice) Good and pure →

471
00:31:14,306 --> 00:31:17,810
Above all, he loved his family.

472
00:31:19,311 --> 00:31:22,815
Now that I know that, I'm relieved.

473
00:31:25,317 --> 00:31:29,822
(Ryoko) Is there no need for me anymore?

474
00:31:31,757 --> 00:31:33,759
(Luna) That's right.

475
00:31:36,262 --> 00:31:38,197
Hope you're well.

476
00:31:38,264 --> 00:31:52,211
♪～

477
00:31:52,278 --> 00:31:54,713
(Tamura) I see…｡

478
00:31:54,780 --> 00:31:58,784
(Ryoko) I was told that I had no intention of seeing her again.

479
00:32:01,287 --> 00:32:08,227
(Tamura) Well, I think one way is to wait a little while.

480
00:32:08,294 --> 00:32:14,733
If you really have a connection with that person, you're sure to connect again someday.

481
00:32:14,800 --> 00:32:16,802
That's what I think.

482
00:32:23,809 --> 00:32:27,746
>> I feel lonely... Are you saying that your partner is going to disappear?

483
00:32:27,813 --> 00:32:29,748
(Kominato) No, no, I'm totally fine.

484
00:32:29,815 --> 00:32:32,251
You're the one who's lonely, right?

485
00:32:36,755 --> 00:32:42,261
Actually, I'm also thinking about my second life.

486
00:32:44,763 --> 00:32:47,700
(Sound of automatic door opening) Ah!

487
00:32:47,766 --> 00:32:52,204
(Ryoko) Mr. Tamura, thank you for everything.

488
00:32:52,271 --> 00:32:54,273
(Tamura) That's it.

489
00:32:58,277 --> 00:33:02,715
📱(vibration sound)

490
00:33:02,781 --> 00:33:05,284
(Tamura) Yes, thank you for your hard work.

491
00:33:06,785 --> 00:33:09,221
Huh?

492
00:33:09,288 --> 00:33:11,223
Ryoko!

493
00:33:11,290 --> 00:33:13,225
Noppy: Looks like you're in Osaka.

494
00:33:13,292 --> 00:33:15,227
Kominato-san just met him.

495
00:33:15,294 --> 00:33:17,730
(Ryoko) Oh, ah... Can I just say that?

496
00:33:17,796 --> 00:33:21,734
Hello, Mr. Kominato? Mom, did you say something?

497
00:33:21,800 --> 00:33:24,236
>> There is a literary spot that I have missed →

498
00:33:24,303 --> 00:33:26,238
He said he came soon.

499
00:33:26,305 --> 00:33:27,740
(Ryoko) Where are you?

500
00:33:27,806 --> 00:33:29,742
>> Ah, I don't know.

501
00:33:29,808 --> 00:33:32,177
I was asked how to ride the Chinchin train.

502
00:33:32,244 --> 00:33:34,179
(Ryoko) A dick train?

503
00:33:34,246 --> 00:33:37,683
(Tamura) Ah, it's a Hankai train. It's a streetcar in Osaka.

504
00:33:37,750 --> 00:33:40,185
(Ryoko) Mom, how was it?

505
00:33:40,252 --> 00:33:43,255
>> I ate Kasu Udon and it looked delicious.

506
00:33:48,927 --> 00:33:51,864
(Ryoko) There are so many Chinchin train stations.

507
00:33:51,930 --> 00:33:54,867
(Monitor) (Caster) I hope it's sunny tomorrow.

508
00:33:54,933 --> 00:33:58,871
(Monitor) Because tomorrow, March 3rd, there will be a total lunar eclipse.

509
00:33:58,937 --> 00:34:01,373
(Monitor) Apparently it can be seen all over Japan.

510
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:03,942
(Monitor) Let's take a look at the weather you're interested in.

511
00:34:08,947 --> 00:34:10,883
(Ryoko) What happened?

512
00:34:10,949 --> 00:34:13,886
(Atsushi) Book review A book recommended by my father.

513
00:34:13,952 --> 00:34:15,888
He said I could take it from the study.

514
00:34:15,954 --> 00:34:18,323
(Ryoko) Ah~ “Snow Country”.

515
00:34:18,390 --> 00:34:21,393
>>Your father is your favorite author.

516
00:34:23,395 --> 00:34:26,331
(Ryoko) Yasunari Kawabata…｡

517
00:34:26,398 --> 00:34:29,334
>> [My teacher also likes Yasunari Kawabata]

518
00:34:29,401 --> 00:34:41,847
♪～

519
00:34:41,914 --> 00:34:45,417
(Ryoko) A literary spot that moms want to go to.

520
00:34:47,419 --> 00:34:50,856
Ah, “the sun and the moon.”

521
00:34:50,923 --> 00:34:52,925
``Gate under the Moon.''

522
00:34:54,426 --> 00:34:56,361
"White full moon"

523
00:34:56,428 --> 00:34:58,864
Ah, “the moon”.

524
00:34:58,931 --> 00:35:23,388
♪～

525
00:35:35,901 --> 00:35:40,906
(birds chirping)

526
00:35:53,418 --> 00:35:55,354
(Ryoko) Ha...

527
00:35:55,420 --> 00:35:57,856
The full moon of the final chapter...

528
00:35:57,923 --> 00:36:00,359
>> [“I want to change the depiction of the moon”]

529
00:36:00,425 --> 00:36:03,362
[They said it would end with a full moon.]

530
00:36:03,428 --> 00:36:05,864
(Ryoko) Yasunari Kawabata…｡

531
00:36:05,931 --> 00:36:09,868
(Atsushi) [Book recommended by my father] [My teacher also likes Yasunari Kawabata]

532
00:36:09,935 --> 00:36:12,371
(Ryoko) Chinchin train...｡

533
00:36:12,437 --> 00:36:14,373
(Kominato) [Because there is a literary spot that I missed →

534
00:36:14,439 --> 00:36:16,808
I'm coming soon]

535
00:36:16,875 --> 00:36:18,810
(Ryoko) March 3rd...

536
00:36:18,877 --> 00:36:21,813
(Monitor) [It's finally a total lunar eclipse]

537
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:23,815
(Luna) [To Ryoko →

538
00:36:23,882 --> 00:36:29,888
I want you to live a life where you can love your choices.]

539
00:36:32,891 --> 00:36:34,893
(Ryoko) We are connected.

540
00:36:37,896 --> 00:36:40,332
>>Ah, what are you here?

541
00:36:40,399 --> 00:36:42,334
What are you doing?

542
00:36:42,401 --> 00:36:47,339
(Ryoko) Hey, literature is amazing.

543
00:36:47,406 --> 00:36:50,409
It will teach you many things.

544
00:36:54,413 --> 00:36:58,850
(Ryoko) Kikuo-san I'm going to Osaka.

545
00:36:58,917 --> 00:37:10,862
♪～

546
00:37:10,929 --> 00:37:12,864
(Ryoko) Oh, sorry.

547
00:37:12,931 --> 00:37:15,367
Do you know where that Chinchin train boarding place is?

548
00:37:15,434 --> 00:37:18,303
>> Ah, Hankai train, it's right after getting off there.

549
00:37:18,370 --> 00:37:21,373
(Ryoko) Over there... Thank you.

550
00:37:26,878 --> 00:37:28,880
(Ryoko) Ha.

551
00:37:32,384 --> 00:37:36,888
(Ryoko) Ha ha ha ha...｡

552
00:37:44,896 --> 00:37:49,401
(Ryoko) ⟨Mom was so beautiful it was scary⟩

553
00:37:54,806 --> 00:38:00,679
(Ryoko) Ha ha ha ha...｡

554
00:38:00,746 --> 00:38:03,181
(Luna) Why here?

555
00:38:03,248 --> 00:38:05,250
(Ryoko) Because we were connected.

556
00:38:06,752 --> 00:38:10,689
Mom went out of her way to return to Osaka once again.

557
00:38:10,756 --> 00:38:14,192
The literary spot I wanted to go to is →

558
00:38:14,259 --> 00:38:19,765
I'm sure it has something to do with the final chapter of the new movie.

559
00:38:22,267 --> 00:38:24,703
Kikuo-san said.

560
00:38:24,770 --> 00:38:30,208
It seems that Professor Shigehara will change the depiction of the moon.

561
00:38:30,275 --> 00:38:35,213
That means it's a place related to the moon.

562
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:39,718
Maybe it's because my mom said she liked it →

563
00:38:39,785 --> 00:38:43,722
I think it might be related to Yasunari Kawabata's novel.

564
00:38:43,789 --> 00:38:49,227
I did some research and came across this Sorihashi bridge.

565
00:38:49,294 --> 00:38:54,733
It also became the title of Yasunari Kawabata's novel →

566
00:38:54,800 --> 00:38:58,670
A famous moon spot in Osaka.

567
00:38:58,737 --> 00:39:04,676
And today, March 3rd, is a lunar eclipse.

568
00:39:04,743 --> 00:39:08,680
A special day for people who love the moon.

569
00:39:08,747 --> 00:39:14,753
So I guess mom will be here tonight.

570
00:39:16,755 --> 00:39:18,690
(Luna) Great job.

571
00:39:18,757 --> 00:39:21,259
But why bother?

572
00:39:24,262 --> 00:39:30,202
(Ryoko) Yasunari Kawabata's short story published shortly after the war →

573
00:39:30,268 --> 00:39:37,709
A trilogy of ``Sorihashi,'' ``Shigure,'' and ``Sumiyoshi.''

574
00:39:37,776 --> 00:39:43,715
"Sumida River" was written 22 years later.

575
00:39:43,782 --> 00:39:50,722
All four of these works started with the same beginning.

576
00:39:50,789 --> 00:39:56,294
"Where are you?"

577
00:39:58,230 --> 00:40:02,734
I mean, I wanted to meet you.

578
00:40:05,237 --> 00:40:07,672
(Luna) Looks like a literature buff.

579
00:40:07,739 --> 00:40:10,242
(Ryoko) I'm sorry.

580
00:40:15,747 --> 00:40:20,185
(Luna) It is said that crossing this Sori Bridge will purify your heart →

581
00:40:20,252 --> 00:40:23,688
Apparently there is a legend.

582
00:40:23,755 --> 00:40:26,191
So now →

583
00:40:26,258 --> 00:40:31,763
I wanted to let go of everything I needed to let go of.

584
00:40:40,272 --> 00:40:44,776
(Ryoko) The moon will be hiding soon.

585
00:40:47,779 --> 00:40:54,219
(Luna) The lunar eclipse is said to be a symbol of reset and rebirth.

586
00:40:54,286 --> 00:41:07,732
♪～

587
00:41:07,799 --> 00:41:10,735
(Luna) Mr. Yasunari Kawabata is →

588
00:41:10,802 --> 00:41:14,239
At the lecture when he won the Nobel Prize →

589
00:41:14,306 --> 00:41:16,241
This is what he said.

590
00:41:16,308 --> 00:41:22,747
``I think of my friends the most during the Setsugetsuhana.''

591
00:41:22,814 --> 00:41:24,816
(Ryoko) What does it mean?

592
00:41:27,819 --> 00:41:32,257
(Luna) Snow and moon flowers.

593
00:41:32,324 --> 00:41:38,263
When people see something beautiful, they remember their friends →

594
00:41:38,330 --> 00:41:44,336
I hope to share the happiness of encountering such beauty.

595
00:41:54,846 --> 00:42:00,285
(Luna) I lied the other day.

596
00:42:02,787 --> 00:42:05,290
Really...

597
00:42:07,792 --> 00:42:10,295
I want to be Ryoko's friend.

598
00:42:17,302 --> 00:42:20,805
(Ryoko) I thought we were friends for a long time.

599
00:42:22,307 --> 00:42:34,753
♪～

600
00:42:34,819 --> 00:42:39,324
(Sound of a car approaching)

601
00:42:43,328 --> 00:42:45,263
(Ryoko) Ah, this car!

602
00:42:45,330 --> 00:42:47,265
(Luna) Now let's go back to Tokyo.

603
00:42:47,332 --> 00:42:51,770
(Ryoko) Good! By the way, is this an expense?

604
00:42:51,836 --> 00:42:54,773
(Luna) Of course. (Ryoko) Hehe.

605
00:42:54,839 --> 00:43:04,215
♪～

606
00:43:04,282 --> 00:43:07,719
(Ryoko) ⟨Everyday life awaits you when you arrive in Tokyo⟩

607
00:43:07,786 --> 00:43:10,722
⟨But don't turn back⟩

608
00:43:10,789 --> 00:43:17,729
⟨Mom and I are going on a new journey⟩

609
00:43:17,796 --> 00:43:21,232
(Ryoko's voice) ``I'm going back to Tokyo with my mom.''

610
00:43:21,299 --> 00:43:23,234
(Tamura) Good.

611
00:43:23,301 --> 00:43:26,805
📱(vibration sound)

612
00:43:28,306 --> 00:43:30,241
(Tamura) Hello?

613
00:43:30,308 --> 00:43:32,243
📱(Mitsuko) You're back here, right?

614
00:43:32,310 --> 00:43:35,814
📱 Did you hear about the director of Nonomiya Hospital?

615
00:43:39,317 --> 00:43:41,820
(Sound of keyboard hitting)

616
00:43:43,321 --> 00:43:57,769
♪～

617
00:43:57,836 --> 00:44:01,706
(Luna) ⟨Ryoko my dear friend⟩

618
00:44:01,773 --> 00:44:06,778
⟨I hoped that only fun things would happen from now on⟩

619
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:13,718
⟨But God still loves us →

620
00:44:13,785 --> 00:44:17,222
It seems like he intends to continue giving trials⟩

621
00:44:17,288 --> 00:44:37,308
♪～
